      <akn:section eId="sec_31_1330">
        <akn:num>31-1330</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Reinsurerâ€™s liability.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_31-1330_1">
      <akn:num>(1)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The contracts or other written agreements specifically provide for another payee of the reinsurance in the event of the insolvency of the ceding insurer; or</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_31-1330_2">
      <akn:num>(2)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The assuming insurer, with the consent of the direct insureds, has assumed the policy obligations of the ceding insurer as the direct obligation of the assuming insurer to the payees under such policies and in substitution for the obligations of the ceding insurer to the payees.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
